        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 6:01PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 601 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Weaver, or near Saks, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Anniston, Oxford, Talladega, Jacksonville, Heflin, Cobb Town, West
End-Cobb Town, Fort McClellan, Saks, Lincoln, Weaver, Ragland,
Munford, Ohatchee, Hobson City, Talladega Superspeedway, Anniston
Regional Airport, Blue Mountain, Alexandria, and Corinth.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
